OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCyber-flashing likely to   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbecome a criminal offence -
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FDorries                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Ministers are working towards making   
OL,6, the unsolicited sending of obscene     
OL,7, images via wi-fi or Bluetooth a        
OL,8, criminal offence, Culture Secretary    
OL,9, Nadine Dorries has said.               
OL,11,FShe told MPs that "cyber-flashing" was 
OL,12,Flikely to be "within the scope" of the 
OL,13,Fupcoming Online Safety Bill.           
OL,15,FAnd she said that online platforms who 
OL,16,Ffailed in their duty of care for users 
OL,17,Fwould face criminal sanctions.         
OL,19,FThey must "change their behaviours     
OL,20,Fnow", Ms Dorries added.                
